        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:13AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 213 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stanford, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stanford and Coffee Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
